                  <persName id="t18250217-152-person854">
                  JOHN 
                  VANN
               <interp inst="t18250217-152-person854" type="surname" value="VANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250217-152-person854" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250217-152-person854" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol of Bow-street. I met the prisoner between six and seven o'clock on the evening of the 2d of February, in Whitechapel, with a basket of tools on his shoulder - I asked what he had got; he said, some tools, and was going to get money on them - it was near a pawnbroker's shop. I took the basket, and it contained carpenters' tools. I asked whose property it was - he said his own.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250217-152-person855">
                  GEORGE 
                  FURLONG
               <interp inst="t18250217-152-person855" type="surname" value="FURLONG"></interp>
